Chapter 44 Had you followed Captain Ahab down into his cabin after the squall that took place on the night succeeding that wild ratification of his purpose with his crew, you would have seen him go to a locker in the transom, and, bringing out a large wrinkled roll of yellowish sea-charts, spread them before him on his screwed-down table.

2
00:00:24,230 --> 00:00:40,023
Then, seating himself before it, you would have seen him intently study the various lines and shadings which there met his eye, and with slow but steady pencil trace additional courses over spaces that before were blank.

3
00:00:40,083 --> 00:00:44,753
At intervals he would refer to piles of old log-books beside him.

4
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:54,428
wherein were set down the seasons, and places in which, on various former voyages of various ships, sperm-whales had been captured or seen.

5
00:00:54,448 --> 00:01:02,640
While thus employed, the heavy pewter lamp suspended in chains over his head, continually rocked with the motion of the ship,

6
00:01:02,620 --> 00:01:23,295
and forever threw shifting gleams and shadows of lines upon his wrinkled brow, till it almost seemed that while he himself was marking out lines and courses on the wrinkled charts, some invisible pencil was also tracing lines and courses upon the deeply marked chart of his forehead.

7
00:01:23,950 --> 00:01:31,441
But it was not this night, in particular, that, in the solitude of his cabin, Ahab thus pondered over his charts.

8
00:01:32,342 --> 00:01:40,194
Almost every night they were brought out, almost every night some pencil marks were effaced, and others were substituted.

9
00:01:40,374 --> 00:01:53,333
For with the charts of all four oceans before him, Ahab was threading a maze of currents and eddies, with a view to the more certain accomplishment of that monomaniac thought of his soul.

10
00:01:53,313 --> 00:02:06,391
Now, to any one not fully acquainted with the ways of the Leviathans, it might seem an absurdly hopeless task thus to seek out one solitary creature in the unhooped oceans of this planet.

11
00:02:06,691 --> 00:02:15,743
But not so did it seem to Ahab, who knew the sets of all tides and currents, and thereby calculating the driftings of the sperm-whale's food,

12
00:02:15,723 --> 00:02:34,525
and, also, calling to mind the regular, ascertain seasons for hunting him in particular latitudes, called, arrive at reasonable surmises, almost approaching to certainties, concerning the timeliest day to be upon this or that ground, in search of his prey.

13
00:02:34,505 --> 00:02:48,238
So assured, indeed, is the fact concerning the periodicalness of the sperm-whales resorting to given waters, that many hunters believe that, could he be closely observed and studied throughout the world.

14
00:02:49,239 --> 00:03:03,972
Were the logs for one voyage of the entire whale-fleet carefully collated, then the migrations of the sperm-whale would be found to correspond in invariability to those of the herring-shoals or the flights of swallows.

15
00:03:03,952 --> 00:03:09,359
On this hint, attempts have been made to construct elaborate migratory charts of the sperm whale.

